==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Underlease
<hw>Un"der*lease</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Law)</fld>
<def>A lease granted by a tenant or lessee; especially, a lease granted
by one who is himself a lessee for years, for any fewer or less number
of years than he himself holds; a sublease.</def>
<rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Underlet</ent>⟦br⟧
